  "prompt": "Why don't girls talk to me, but talk to everyone else?",
  "response": "It's tough to pinpoint the exact reasons without more context, as social interactions can be influenced by a wide variety of factors. However, here are some possibilities to consider:\n\n1. **Social Skills**: Evaluate how you approach conversations. Are you confident, respectful, and engaging? Sometimes improving social skills can make a big difference.\n\n2. **Body Language**: Non-verbal cues play a significant role in communication. Ensure you're approachable, smile, and maintain good eye contact.\n\n3. **Confidence and Self-Esteem**: Confidence can be very attractive. Work on building your self-esteem and becoming comfortable in social settings.\n\n4. **Common Interests**: Try finding common ground and shared interests with girls to spark conversations.\n\n5. **Feedback**: If possible, ask friends for feedback on your interactions. They might offer valuable insights.\n\n6. **Respect Boundaries**: Make sure you're not coming off too strong or invading personal space, which can be off-putting.\n\n7. **Environmental Factors**: Consider the settings where you're trying to initiate conversations. Certain environments may be more conducive to socializing.\n\nImproving social interactions takes time and practice, so be patient with yourself as you work on these aspects.",
